Description: Limestone ostracon: on the recto two columns of respectively five and seven incomplete lines of a text of unknown character (a legal report?). On the verso three lines of a text, possibly a continuation of the text on the recto.
Curator's comments: This text might concern the misdeeds of the well-known son of Menna, Merysekhmet, for whom see J.J. Janssen in R.J. Demaree and JJ. Janssen (eds), 'Gleanings from Deir el-Medîna' (Leiden, 1982), pp. 116ff.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136404) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136404)
